The '''Department of Antiquities''' is a [[government department]] of the [[Republic of Cyprus]] with responsibility for [[Archaeology|archaeological research]] and [[cultural heritage management]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mcw.gov.cy/mcw/da/da.nsf/DMLmission_en/DMLmission_en?OpenDocument|title=Mission / Authorities|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Department of Antiquities|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-02-10}}</ref> It was established in 1935 by the [[British Cyprus (1878–1960)|British colonial government]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mcw.gov.cy/mcw/da/da.nsf/DMLhistory_en/DMLhistory_en?OpenDocument|title=Historical Background|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Department of Antiquities|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-02-10}}</ref>
